# Allowlist: central scripts with known provider/OS coupling and bash shebangs.
#
# Format:
#   <path>:<reason>
#
# Reason prefixes determine which check accepts the entry:
#   provider/OS reference - ...  — accepted by the provider/OS ID check
#   bash shebang - ...           — accepted by the bash language policy check
#
# Each entry is a TODO for future porting / Part 2 plugin relocation.

# --- Provider/OS coupling ---
scripts/catalog-options:provider/OS reference - provider-specific OS image metadata gating - Part 2 moves key checks into provider plugins
scripts/config-env:provider/OS reference - provider-to-config-key mapping - Part 2 moves into provider plugin config
scripts/config-migrate:provider/OS reference - provider-to-config-key mapping - Part 2 moves into provider plugin config
scripts/doctor:provider/OS reference - provider-specific CLI tool checks - Part 2 moves into provider plugins
scripts/instance-create:provider/OS reference - provider-specific CLI usage hints - Part 2 derives from provider manifests
scripts/instance-password:provider/OS reference - vultr-specific password retrieval - Part 2 moves into vultr plugin
scripts/instance-profile-overlay:provider/OS reference - raspberry-pi host validation - Part 2 moves into raspberry-pi plugin
scripts/instance-resolve:provider/OS reference - provider-specific OS key validation - Part 2 moves into per-plugin validate hooks
scripts/package-provision:provider/OS reference - raspberry-pi password handling - Part 2 moves into raspberry-pi plugin
scripts/profile-resolve:provider/OS reference - provider-specific env emission - Part 2 moves into provider plugins
scripts/providers-status:provider/OS reference - provider-specific connectivity checks - Part 2 moves into provider plugins
scripts/provision:provider/OS reference - vultr-specific password retrieval - Part 2 moves into vultr plugin
scripts/remote-console:provider/OS reference - local-qemu not-implemented guard - Part 2 moves into local-qemu plugin
scripts/remote-waypipe:provider/OS reference - raspberry-pi IP handling - Part 2 moves into raspberry-pi plugin
scripts/vagrant-up:provider/OS reference - local-qemu Vagrant dispatch - Part 2 moves into local-qemu plugin

# --- Bash shebangs (language policy: no new bash in scripts/) ---
